Now I have the full picture. Here's what changed and how to fix each piece:

---

## Root Cause

.NET 10's `Microsoft.AspNetCore.OpenApi` upgraded to **Microsoft.OpenApi v2.0**, which targets **OpenAPI 3.1** and has several breaking changes.

---

### 1. `OpenApiString` / `OpenApiAny` types → `JsonNode`

The entire `Microsoft.OpenApi.Any` namespace is gone. Use `System.Text.Json.Nodes` instead.

```diff
- using Microsoft.OpenApi.Any;
+ using System.Text.Json.Nodes;

- param.Schema.Example = new OpenApiString("1.0");
+ param.Schema.Example = JsonValue.Create("1.0");
```

For complex examples, use `JsonObject` instead of `OpenApiObject`:

```diff
- schema.Example = new OpenApiObject
-     { ["key"] = new OpenApiString("value"), ["num"] = new OpenApiInteger(42) };
+ schema.Example = new JsonObject
+     { ["key"] = "value", ["num"] = 42 };
```

---

### 2. `schema.Nullable` property removed

OpenAPI 3.1 represents nullability via the `type` array (e.g., `["string", "null"]`). The `Nullable` property no longer exists on `OpenApiSchema`. Instead, check/set the `Type` flags:

```diff
- property.Value.Nullable = false;
+ // Remove JsonSchemaType.Null from the type flags
+ if (property.Value.Type.HasValue)
+     property.Value.Type = property.Value.Type.Value & ~JsonSchemaType.Null;
```

> `JsonSchemaType` is in the `Microsoft.OpenApi.Models` namespace.

To **set** nullable:
```csharp
schema.Type = schema.Type | JsonSchemaType.Null;
```

---

### 3. `operation.Responses` — no change needed

`operation.Responses.TryAdd("401", new OpenApiResponse { ... })` still compiles as-is. ✅

---

### 4. `OpenApiSecurityScheme` with `Reference` + `OpenApiSecurityRequirement` as dictionary

In OpenApi v2, `OpenApiSecurityRequirement` **still works as a dictionary**, and this pattern remains valid per the [official .NET 10 docs](https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/aspnet/core/fundamentals/openapi/customize-openapi?view=aspnetcore-10.0). No change needed here. ✅

---

### Fixed Code

```csharp
using System.Text.Json.Nodes;       // replaces Microsoft.OpenApi.Any
using Microsoft.OpenApi.Models;

options.AddOperationTransformer((operation, context, ct) =>
{
    var param = operation.Parameters?.FirstOrDefault(p => p.Name == "api-version");
    if (param is not null)
    {
        param.Schema.Example = JsonValue.Create("1.0");  // was new OpenApiString(...)
    }

    operation.Responses ??= new OpenApiResponses();
    operation.Responses.TryAdd("401", new OpenApiResponse { Description = "Unauthorized" });

    var oAuthScheme = new OpenApiSecurityScheme
    {
        Reference = new OpenApiReference { Type = ReferenceType.SecurityScheme, Id = "oauth2" }
    };
    operation.Security = new List<OpenApiSecurityRequirement>
    {
        new() { [oAuthScheme] = scopes }
    };

    return Task.CompletedTask;
});

options.AddSchemaTransformer((schema, context, ct) =>
{
    if (schema.Properties is not null)
    {
        foreach (var property in schema.Properties)
        {
            if (schema.Required?.Contains(property.Key) != true)
            {
                // was: property.Value.Nullable = false;
                if (property.Value.Type.HasValue)
                    property.Value.Type = property.Value.Type.Value & ~JsonSchemaType.Null;
            }
        }
    }
    return Task.CompletedTask;
});
```

### Summary of changes

| .NET 9 (OpenApi v1) | .NET 10 (OpenApi v2) |
|---|---|
| `using Microsoft.OpenApi.Any` | `using System.Text.Json.Nodes` |
| `new OpenApiString("...")` | `JsonValue.Create("...")` |
| `new OpenApiObject { ... }` | `new JsonObject { ... }` |
| `schema.Nullable = true/false` | Set/clear `JsonSchemaType.Null` in `schema.Type` |
